"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-07-paris-2024-olympics-nigeria-get-tough-draw-in-4x100m-relays\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Nigeria 4x100m relay teams have been handed tough draws in the men and women's categories.  The men's team will be up against USA, Great Britain, and Japan.  The duo of Kanyinsola Ajayi and Favour Ashe will spearhead Nigeria's charge for medal in the event.  The women's team will clash with Great Britain, France and Jamaica.  Favour Ofili will be hoping to win a medal in the event after the disappointment of her outing in the women's 200m final.  The semi-finals is slated for Stade de France on Friday.  EPL: Paul Scholes happy over ex-Man Utd attacker's return to Old Trafford  EPL: Maresca names three 'very important' Chelsea players  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"